HDFS Commands :-
Create directories in HDFS :-  hdfs dfs -mkdir /user/cloudera/data
Create an empty file in HDFS :- hdfs dfs -touchz /user/cloudera/data/file1.txt
Add the content to the file. :- echo "this is my content" | hdfs dfs - appendToFile - /user/cloudera/data/file1.txt
Copy file from local to HDFS :- hdfs dfs -copyFromLocal localfile.txt /user/cloudera/ 
Copy file from HDFS to local :- hdfs dfs -copyToLocal /user/cloudera/file1.txt ./ 
Move (not copy) file from local to HDFS :- hdfs dfs -moveFromLocal localfile.txt /user/cloudera/ 
Copy file within HDFS :- hdfs dfs -cp /user/cloudera/file1.txt /user/hadoop/ 
Move file within HDFS :- hdfs dfs -mv /user/cloudera/file1.txt /user/hadoop/
Delete a file :- hdfs dfs -rm /user/cloudera/file1.txt 
Delete a directory recursively :- hdfs dfs -rm -r /user/cloudera/data/
Show file/directory size :- hdfs dfs -du /user/cloudera/ 
Show total size summary :- hdfs dfs -dus /user/cloudera/ 
Display file metadata :- hdfs dfs -stat /user/cloudera/file1.txt
